Creating the variables

In[65]:
#Create x and y variables
x = cds.drop('diagnosis', axis=1).to_numpy()
y = cds['diagnosis'].to_numpy()

Creating Test and Train data

In[66]:
#Create Training and Test Datasets
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
x_train, x_test,y_train, y_test = train_test_split(x, y, stratify = y,test_size=0.2,random_state=0)

Scaling the Data

In[67]:
#Scale the Data
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler
sc = StandardScaler()
x_train2 = sc.fit_transform(x_train)
x_test2 = sc.transform(x_test)

Creating the model - SVM & Naive Bayes

In[68]:
#Script for SVM and NB
from sklearn.svm import SVC
from sklearn.naive_bayes import GaussianNB
from sklearn.metrics import classification_report, confusion_matrix  

for name,method in [('SVM', SVC(kernel='linear',random_state=0)),('Naive Bayes',GaussianNB())]: 
    method.fit(x_train2,y_train)
    predict = method.predict(x_test2)
    print('\nEstimator: {}'.format(name))
    print(confusion_matrix(y_test,predict))
    print(classification_report(y_test,predict))

Finding the best fit for SVM using Non-linear

In[70]:
#find the best hyper parameters using non-linear 
from sklearn.model_selection import GridSearchCV
param_grid = {'C':[0.1,1,10,100,1000],'gamma':[1,0.1,0.01,0.001,0.001], 'kernel':['rbf']}
grid = GridSearchCV(SVC(),param_grid,verbose = 4)
grid.fit(x_train,y_train)
grid.best_params_
grid.best_estimator_
grid_predictions = grid.predict(x_test)
cmG = confusion_matrix(y_test,grid_predictions)
sns.heatmap(cmG, annot=True)
plt.title('Confusion Matrix - Non-linear SVM Kernel')
print(confusion_matrix(y_test,grid_predictions))
print(classification_report(y_test,grid_predictions))
